NAVIGATION


CREATE A NAVIGATION STRUCTURE

@db-ux/astro comes with a built-in navigation menu that is included in most
layouts. This navigation allows users to easily browse through the different
pages of your website. As of now, this navigation is not generated
automatically. Instead, you need to manually configure which pages should appear
in the navigation.

We recommend creating a new file in your app that will hold your navigation
structure. You can find an example here [/apps/astro/src/app.navigation.ts]. The
file name or location is not important, but we recommend placing it in the src
directory of your Astro project for easy access.

// src/app.navigation.ts
export const navigation: NavigationItem[] = [
  {
    title: 'Guides',
    children: [
      {
        title: 'Getting Started',
        path: '/guides/getting-started',
      },
      {
        title: 'Navigation',
        path: '/guides/navigation',
      },
    ],
  },
  {
    title: 'Layouts',
    children: [
      {
        title: 'Default Layout',
        path: '/layouts/default',
      },
    ],
  }
];

After doing so, you can import that navigation structure in astro.config.mjs and
pass it to the integration config.

// astro.config.mjs
import { defineConfig } from 'astro/config';
import { dbUxAstro } from '@db-ux/astro';
import { navigation } from './src/app.navigation';

export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [
    dbUxAstro({
      // Other config options...
      navigation,
    }),
  ],
  // Other config options...
});

The integration will then use your navigation structure to render the navigation
menu in the application header.

